This is the SSHF web UI: a Next.js 15 App Router application (React 18, MUI v6).
It authenticates users with Google domain accounts and talks to the SSHF REST API over HTTPS using bearer tokens.
All backend data access goes through the shared API client in `src/lib/api.js`; the UI never contacts CouchDB directly.
Requests and responses are JSON and must follow the contract documented in `docs/openapi.json`.
Always use ES module syntax. Prefer React function components and the `@/*` path alias (maps to `src/`).

For rule grouping and conflict precedence, see `rules/index.mdc`.
